body:
Added an argument for "-stats" option to specify the top n heavy hitters.
@deroneriksson - is this useful in general?
@niketanpansare, @bertholdreinwald - this will help with the gpu performance investigation.

To reproduce this bug, please try following DML script:
z = matrix (0, rows = 2, cols = 5);
z[2, 2] = 2.5;
z[2, 3] = 5.0;
z[2, 4] = 10.0;
n = ncol(z);
print ("ncol (z) = " + ncol (z) + ", but n = " + n);

This prints ncol (z) = 5, but n = 1.

@bertholdreinwald @asurve @mboehm7

@niketanpansare, @mboehm7, @bertholdreinwald, @iyounus
This initial implementation is keeping in line with the discussion on the dev mailing list.
The CP 'svd' function is implemented and backed by Apache Commons Math.

To reproduce this bug, please use following scripts:

Works as expected:

``` bash
for(i in seq(1,5,1)) {
        print(i)
}
for(i in 1:5) {
        print(i)
}
```

Doesnot work:

``` bash
for(i in seq(1,5)) {
        print(i)
}
```
